cyclone.name: HUMBERTO
cyclone.current_location: about 130 mi ESE of Great Abaco Island
cyclone.trajectory: Moving northwest then turning north-northwest, projected to track just offshore the Florida east coast this weekend before accelerating northward toward the Carolina coast and open Atlantic early next week

port.name: Port of Palm Beach District, FL

weather_observation.watch_coast: No watches in effect along the Florida east coast
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical Storm Warning for the northwestern Bahamas excluding Andros Island

weather_observation.wind: Low (15%) chance of sustained tropical-storm-force (≥34 kt) winds; occasional gusts possible as the center passes offshore late Saturday into Sunday
